*** THIS PROJECT IS STILL UNDER DEVELOPMENT ***r
r
1) Install vagrant, VirtualBox  and download lucid32 base boxr
r
This project is a simple Vagrant lucid32 server, so before you start you will need to install vagrant and VirtualBox. These are both very popular software and the latest version can installed in a couple of minutes ... just google it!r
Next download the lucid32.box:r
r
  vagrant box add lucid32 http://files.vagrantup.com/lucid32.boxr
r
FYI ... vagrant will save the 249M box file in a hidden directory:r
r
  $ cd ~/.vagrant.d/boxesr
  $ ls -ltrr
  drwxr-xr-x  5 dpitts  660531311  170 Apr  9 22:43 lucid32r
  $ du -hr
  249M  ./lucid32r
r
2) Clone this repor
r
3) Go to the repo and launch the boxr
r
  cd [repo]r
  vagrant upr
